# TORP UI Rules

## Visual system

- Default to **dark zinc** surfaces: `bg-zinc-950` page, `bg-zinc-900` elevated, `border-zinc-800/900` separators, `text-zinc-100` primary text, `text-zinc-400` secondary.
- Primary CTA: **`bg-white text-black`** (hover `bg-zinc-200`). Avoid neon gradients unless explicitly requested.
- Secondary CTA: `bg-zinc-800 hover:bg-zinc-700 text-white`.

## Typography

- Treat `index.html` as the source of truth for font behavior.
- Headings/buttons: display stack + uppercase feel.
- Paragraphs/forms/small text: **Inter**, normal casing — do not force uppercase on long copy.

## Layout + spacing

- Prefer large section padding (`py-24`–`py-32`) on marketing pages.
- Keep layouts airy: use `max-w-*` content columns instead of filling the full width with text.

## Motion

- Prefer subtle transitions (`duration-300`–`700`). Avoid aggressive springs.

## Dashboard specifics

- Keep HQ UI **high-contrast and restrained**; use accent colors only for semantic states (paid/pending/error).

## Modals

- Use `fixed inset-0` + `bg-black/80+` + `backdrop-blur-*` + `rounded-2xl` panels with `border-zinc-800`.
